<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/21575985-kirill-petrovsky"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1371996251i/21575985._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/21575985-kirill-petrovsky">Kirill Petrovsky</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I watched the election closely (as well as 538&apos;s forecasts) and they were quite correct. On election day they had Trump at approx 30% of winning - and<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I watched the election closely (as well as 538's forecasts) and they were quite correct. On election day they had Trump at approx 30% of winning - and that scenario fulfilled itself.<br />So I'd say that this book will teach you exactly that - what predictions mean and how to understand them.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
